rr

q2_df = read_excel(_song_contest_1975_2019v3.xlsx) q2_df r NA

selecting form country and points to convert to long data since we are intrested with the number of points each country give not the number of points each country recieves

rr

q2_df\(`semi-final` = as.factor(q2_df\)semi-final) q2_df\(Edition =as.factor(q2_df\)Edition) q2_df\(Jury_or_Televoting = as.factor(q2_df\)Jury_or_Televoting) q2_df\(From_country = as.factor(q2_df\)From_country) q2_df\(To_country = as.factor(q2_df\)To_country)

To combine data for multiple years, use mean as an aggregation function.

rr df_countries1 =q2_df %>% filter(semi-final == %>% group_by(Year,Jury_or_Televoting, From_country,To_country) %>% summarise(mean_points = mean(Points, na.rm=TRUE) )

df_countries1 r NA

grouped by from_country variable using from dplyr package. this enabled us to convert the dataset to a long format.

rr df_countries_wide <- df_countries1 %>%
spread(From_country, mean_points) df_countries_wide r NA

scaling the countires dataset to standardize it.

rr df_countries_wide[is.na(df_countries_wide)] = 0
